    <div>
        <h1>Create New Campaign in Phishsims</h1>

        <ol class="steps">
            <li>
                <h2>Accessing the Campaign Creation Page</h2>
                <p>Log in to your Phishsims account.</p>
                <p>Navigate to the main menu on dashboard where Campaign options are available.</p>
                <p>Look for a button labeled "New Campaign" and click on it</p>         
                <img src="/img/Campaign1.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
                
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Entering Campaign Details</h2>
            <h4>STEP-1</h4>
                <p>Click on the "New Campaign" button to access the campaign creation page.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign2.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <h4>STEP-2</h4>
                <p>Provide a unique and descriptive name for your campaign in the designated field.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign3.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-3</h4>
            <p>Select the template category of the campaign from the available options(e.g., Email, SMS,and WhatsApp)..</p>
                <img src="/img/Campaign5.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-4</h4>
            <p>Then select the Template of the campaign from the available options.</p>
            <p>For more information about How to create Template, <a href="/template-content" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign6.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-5</h4>
            <p>After that select the return page of the campaign from the available options.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign7.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-6</h4>
            <p>Then write a senders mail id, subject and description for the campaign</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign8.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-7</h4>
            <p>After writing tha above fields, Select the Category of the campaign from the available options.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign8.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-8</h4>
            <p>Now Schedule a date and time to run the campaign also can select for now to run it.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign9.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            </li>

            <li>
            <h2>Defining Target Audience</h2>
            <h4>STEP-1</h4>
            <p>To import users you can select multiple options to import the users(CSV, Azure Active Directory and OnPrimiseAD)</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign10.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-2</h4>
            <p>After selecting, click on ChooseFile Button</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign11.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-3</h4>
            <p>Choose your file from your PC if you selected CSV and click on open.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign12.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-4</h4>
            <p>After choosing, all the imported users will be visible onthe screen.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign13.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            </li>

        <li>
            <h2>Defining Training to the Users</h2>
            <h4>STEP-1</h4>
            <p>To provide trainig to the phished users, you can select the Add Training option.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign14.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
            <h4>STEP-2</h4>
            <p>After selecting, click on the trainings shown which you want to provide to the users</p>
            <p>For more information about How to create Training, <a href="https://example.com/campaign-types" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign15.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
        </li>

        <li>
            <h2>Saving the Campaign</h2>
            <p>After completing all the above steps, click on SAVE button.</p>
            <p>After Clicking, you will get the popup message for capmpaign creation success.</p>
            <img src="/img/Campaign16.png" alt="Screenshot of entering campaign details">
        </li>


        <h2>Editing Campaign</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Access Campaign: Log in and navigate to the "Campaigns" section, open drop down and click on "All Campaigns" button.</li>
            <img src="/img/Campaign17.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Find Campaign: Locate the Campaign you wish to edit from the list.</li>
            <img src="/img/Campaign18.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Edit Option: Click on the edit option next to the Campaign name.</li>
            <img src="/img/Campaign19.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Modify Content: Use the editor to make changes to the Campaign content.</li>
            
            <li>Save Changes: After editing, save the changes to update the template.</li>
           
        </ol>

            <!-- Include other steps here -->
        </ol>
    </div>

